%N A394409 Pascal-like triangle read by rows: top entry is 2; thereafter fill in entries from top to bottom, alternating between left to right and right to left, with the smallest number that is not yet in the sequence and has a common factor with any earlier entry that is adjacent to it in the triangle.
%C A394409 This is a variation of A397219 where the rows are filled from left to right and then right to left as the triangle is filled from the top. See that sequence for further details.
%C A394409 It is conjectured that every number greater than 1 appears.
%H A394409 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A394409/b394409.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000</a>
